Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Bring a large #saucepan{} of water with @salt{1/2%tsp} to the boil.

Peel the @Baking Potato{1} and slice into 1cm thick rounds.

Once boiling, add the potato slices to the water and simmer until you can easily slip a knife through, ~{8-12%mins}. Carefully drain in a #colander{} and set aside.

Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

While the potatoes cook, heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @Diced British Chicken Thigh{210g}, season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}, and cook until browned all over, ~{3-4%mins}. Turn occasionally.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Transfer the chicken to a #bowl{} and set aside.

Trim the @Carrot{2}, then halve lengthways (no need to peel). Chop into roughly 1cm wide, 5cm long batons.

Pop the carrots onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @olive oil{2%tbsp}, season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer. Roast on the top shelf of your oven until tender, ~{20-25%mins}. Turn halfway through.

In a small bowl, combine the @Panko Breadcrumbs{25%g} and olive oil for the crumb (see pantry for amount). Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{} and set aside.

Return the now empty frying pan to medium-high heat with a drizzle of oil. Once hot, add the @Sliced Mushrooms{80%g} to the pan. Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{} and fry until browned, ~{5-6%mins}, stirring occasionally. Stir in the garlic and cook for ~{1%min}.

Add the @Water for the Sauce{100%ml} and @Chicken Stock Paste{10%g}. Return the chicken to the pan, then bring to the boil. Mix in the @Creme Fraiche{150%g} and @Grated Hard Italian Style Cheese{20%g}, then turn down the heat and simmer gently until thickened, ~{3-4%mins}. Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Transfer the chicken and mushroom filling to an appropriately sized #ovenproof dish{}. Layer on the cooked potato slices, then sprinkle over the crumb.

Season with @ground black pepper{} and bake on the top shelf of your oven until golden brown, ~{10-12%mins}.

When ready, serve your hotpot on plates with the roasted carrots alongside.

Enjoy!